lzh_formatted:
  title: 謾成
  author: 李冑
  language: lzh
  text: 老㤼風霜病益頑。一簷朝旭坐蒲團。隣僧去後門還掩。只有山雲過石欄。
korean:
  title: 만성
  author: 이주
  language: kor
  text: |-
    풍상에 늙은 겁은 병에 더욱 굳어지고
    한 처마 아침 볓에 포단 위에 앉았어라
    이웃 중 간 뒤에 문은 도로 닫혔으니
    다만 메 구름이 돌 난간을 지나치네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0400&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Carelessly Composed
  author: Lee Ju
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Weathered by frost and time, my stubborn ailments deepen.
    I sit upon my meditation mat in the morning sun at the eaves.
    After my neighbor monk departs, the gate closes again behind him.
    Only mountain clouds drift past the stone balustrade.
  footnotes:
    - The poet sits in contemplative solitude, the morning light offering temporary solace to a body worn by age and hardship.
    - The closing gate symbolizes the poet's increasing isolation and withdrawal from the world, with only nature—the passing clouds—as companionship.
